        <h1 id="introduction">Introduction</h1>
<p>Complete API documentation for SitePilot ERP system including materials, suppliers, purchase orders, payments, and project management.</p>
<aside>
    <strong>Base URL</strong>: <code>http://sitepilot/</code>
</aside>
<pre><code>This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

&lt;aside&gt;As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile).
You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).&lt;/aside&gt;</code></pre>

        <h1 id="authenticating-requests">Authenticating requests</h1>
<p>To authenticate requests, include an <strong><code>Authorization</code></strong> header with the value <strong><code>"Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}"</code></strong>.</p>
<p>All authenticated endpoints are marked with a <code>requires authentication</code> badge in the documentation below.</p>
<p>Use Laravel Sanctum Bearer token. Authenticate via /api/login endpoint to get your token.</p>

        <h1 id="activities">Activities</h1>

    <p>Endpoints for activity management including creation, completion tracking, and progress monitoring</p>

                                <h2 id="activities-GETapi-activities">GET api/activities</h2>

<p>
<small class="badge badge-darkred">requires authentication</small>
</p>



<span id="example-requests-GETapi-activities">
<blockquote>Example request:</blockquote>


<div class="bash-example">
    <pre><code class="language-bash">curl --request GET \
    --get "http://sitepilot/api/activities" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"</code></pre></div>


<div class="javascript-example">
    <pre><code class="language-javascript">const url = new URL(
    "http://sitepilot/api/activities"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};


fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response =&gt; response.json());</code></pre></div>

